(90, 2, 'I have high blood pressure. Should I take Aspirin before my workout?', 'According to the database, individuals with high blood pressure should consult with their healthcare professional before taking any medication, including aspirin, before a workout. Aspirin can help thin the blood and reduce blood pressure, but it may not be suitable for everyone, especially those with certain medical conditions or taking certain medications.\n\nIn general, it\'s recommended to avoid taking aspirin before a workout, especially if you have high blood pressure, unless your healthcare professional has specifically advised you to do so. Instead, focus on incorporating regular physical activity, such as cardio and strength training, into your routine to help lower your blood pressure and improve overall cardiovascular health.\n\nIt\'s essential to consult with your healthcare professional before starting any new exercise program, especially if you have any underlying medical conditions. They can provide personalized guidance and recommendations to ensure your safety and well-being.\n\nIn your case, since you have high blood pressure, I recommend consulting with your healthcare professional before taking any medication, including aspirin, before a workout. They can help you develop a safe and effective exercise plan that takes into account your medical condition.', '2026-04-25 07:36:28', '2026-04-25 07:36:28'),
